PSR J1618-4624 has a reasonably short orbital period of 1.78 days. This pulsar has a moderate-sized companion with a minimum mass of 0.5748 solar masses.

It has a low magnetic field strength of 2.71e+08 G. It was discovered in 2011 as part of several minor surveys. PSR J2302+4442 has a very wide orbital period of 125.935 days and a mildly eccentric orbit with an eccentricity of 0.000503021. This pulsar has a low-mass companion with a minimum mass of 0.292 solar masses.
